args: Oh baby, today's snacks look gooood.\nI'm diggin' in!
Yeah. We don't have any fiend-eliminating\nassignments to worry about, so let's enjoy\nit while we can.
Yep! Nothing better than a peaceful day\nand a face full of food. *chomp*
Now that I'm thinking about it,\nwe've had a lot of days like this recently.
Hey, yeah. Maybe the world finally\nstopped going bananas or whatever.
The villages haven't reported any trouble,\neither. Hmm... I wonder...
Uh oh. You've got your thinky face on.
Well, don't you think it's a little odd?\nIt's not like we've solved all of Alberia's\nproblems recently or anything.
I can't believe you're complaining about a\nLACK of fiends.
Wait a sec... Wait just one hot second!\nYou don't think this has anything to do\nwith those rumors, do you?
The rumors, man! The ones about a super\nawesome dragon that's going around layin'\nthe hurt on bad guys and fiends alike!
Maybe our vigilante dragon friend\nhas all the evildoers on the run.
Huh. I'd like to meet this dragon.
Well then, let's go! Not like we've got\nanything else to do today.
It might even be willing to work with us\nin some kind of permanent arrangement.
Right then—we're off to find a dragon!
...Okay, so the first time I heard the rumor\nwas in this village here.
Hmm... Nope. No dragon. Everything looks\nto be nice and quiet around he—
Bwa ha ha! Just lookit all the coin ya\ngots in this here shop'a yours!
Folks spend more what when they ain't\nscared—and that means there's more\nfor us to take! Bwaaaa ha ha ha!
Please, no! I need that money to\nput food on my family's table!
Whazzat, little girl? You backtalkin' us?
The scream came from this shop!
Then let's get in there and save—
Couple of thugs beatin' up on a young\nshopkeeper? Pathetic.
Oy, we ain't pathetic! I'll show ya who's...\nBlimey, but this thing's huge...\nand it gots a TAIL?!
Them horns on its head ain't clip-ons...
If it's a fight you're looking for,\nI'll happily give it to you.
I'm Marishiten, by the way.\nFolks call me the dragon of battle.
Run awaaaay! It's gonna eat uuuuuus!
Please. I'd never eat you.\nI don't enjoy chickens.
Th-thank you for saving me,\nO mighty dragon!
Here's the money they tried to take.\nThat was nearly a disaster, eh?
Right then. Looks like we're done here.
Yeah? Whatcha want? ...Hey, wait.\nI know you. You're that Alberian...
Ah, how wonderful to see you again,\nPrince {player_name}!
Those of the Wyrmclans pledge themselves to\ndragons in the form of a soulpact. This allows\nthem to harbor the power of the dragon within.
Ieyasu has made a soulpact with Marishiten,\nalso known as the dragon of battle.
Ieyasu! When did you arrive here?!
Several days ago. We were actually\non our way to your castle, but...
Well, I could not idly stand by and\npermit such an injustice to occur.
I'd expect nothing less from you.\nBut why turn yourself into a dragon?
The greatest victory is one gained\nwithout bloodshed.
There's no need for me to cross swords\nwith a local oaf when I can scare him\naway with a mere glimpse of my dragon.
Wait a second... The dragon we keep\nhearing about in rumors is YOU?!
Stories are flying about a dragon that's\nbeen punishing fiends and criminals.
But Ieyasu, you're the candidate to be the\nnext shogun. Is it really okay for you to\nbe so far away from Hinomoto?
I have left my territories in\nmore-than-capable hands.
After all, it is necessary to learn of other\ncountries in order to develop one's own.
When I visited this land over the new year,\nI became quite interested in your concept\nof nation-building.
If it's not too much trouble, I'd hoped\nto spend some time with you in order\nto learn a few things.
